The paper deals with the Graph Isomorphism Problem for unit square graphs, which are intersection graphs of axis-parallel unit squares in the plane. This makes it likely to belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions that the recognition problem for this class of graphs is NP-hard, which suggests that it could also belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The paper also discusses new techniques for solving the isomorphism problem, which could make it relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of group theoretic algorithms suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with graph classes and their properties, which could make it relevant to the Discrete Structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
